<strong>💡 Key takeaway:</strong> At the April 2026 Ofgem price cap rate of 24.67p/kWh, charging an EV at home costs roughly 7p per mile. On a smart EV tariff at 8p/kWh, that drops to just 2.3p per mile — compared to around 14–16p per mile for petrol.
